    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "2. Lighting/turn signal switch removal"
    },
    {
      "type": "figure",
      "asset": "960_3.0_jpn_11287937_2.0_disp.png"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Disconnect the coupler (A). Remove the lighting/turn signal switch (C) by pressing the tab (B) and sliding it to the side."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "3. Installation Precautions"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Installation is the reverse of the removal procedure."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 3,
      "text": "1. Lighting/turn signal switch Check"
    },
    {
      "type": "step",
      "number": "1",
      "text": "Inspect for continuity between terminals at each position and confirm that there is continuity only between ○ and ○. If continuity is abnormal, replace the lighting/turn signal switch."
    },
